Summary: This chunk describes properties related to angular and linear damping within an Area3D.

Property: `angular_damp` (float) = `0.1`
Method: `set_angular_damp(value: float) -> void`
Method: `get_angular_damp() -> float`
Description: The rate at which objects stop spinning in this area. Represents the angular velocity lost per second. See ProjectSettings.physics/3d/default_angular_damp for more details about damping.

Property: `angular_damp_space_override` (SpaceOverride) = `0`
Method: `set_angular_damp_space_override_mode(value: SpaceOverride) -> void`
Method: `get_angular_damp_space_override_mode() -> SpaceOverride`
Description: Override mode for angular damping calculations within this area.

Property: `linear_damp` (float) = `0.1`
Method: `set_linear_damp(value: float) -> void`
Method: `get_linear_damp() -> float`
Description: The rate at which objects stop moving in this area. Represents the linear velocity lost per second. See ProjectSettings.physics/3d/default_linear_damp for more details about damping.

Property: `linear_damp_space_override` (SpaceOverride) = `0`
Method: `set_linear_damp_space_override_mode(value: SpaceOverride) -> void`
Method: `get_linear_damp_space_override_mode() -> SpaceOverride`
Description: Override mode for linear damping calculations within this area.
